      <div class="article-teaser">
        <p>You only need to pay once, no matter how many times you drive in and out of the Congestion Charge zone on the same day.</p>
        
      </div>
    
    
      <p>You can pay in advance, on the day of travel or by midnight the following charging day. <strong>The daily charge is &pound;11.50 if you pay in advance or on the same day, or &pound;14 if paid the following charging day.</strong></p>

<p>If you don't pay by midnight on the charging day after you drove in the zone, you'll get a Penalty Charge Notice (PCN).</p>

<p>Not all drivers have to pay. <a href="/modes/driving/congestion-charge/discounts-and-exemptions"> Find out about discounts and exemptions.</a></p>

<p>You can pay the Congestion Charge in several ways. It's quickest and easiest if you <a href="/modes/driving/auto-pay">set up Auto Pay</a>.</p>
      
           
      
